============================================================
Is |Δα₁| = 5 impossible under single arc flip at n=5?
============================================================

Flipping arc (i,j) at n=5 affects:
  - 3-cycles on triples {i,j,k}: at most 3 triples
  - 5-cycles on {0,1,2,3,4}: the single full set
  |Δ(3-cycles)| ≤ 3, |Δ(5-cycles)| ≤ 3
  |Δα₁| = |Δ(3-cyc) + Δ(5-cyc)| ≤ 6
  But |Δα₁| = 5 never occurs (ΔH = ±10 gap)

This suggests a PARITY CONSTRAINT on Δ(3-cyc) ± Δ(5-cyc).

